description:
Sean Johnston has been DJ'ing since his formative years in the frozen North. Acid House Veteran, Techno Survivor, Hardway Bros, Beard Scientist and Freelance Disco Consultant he has played at some of London's landmark clubs including The Promised Land, Sabre Sonic, Club UK, Final Frontier, Disco Bloodbath and was one of the founding residents at London Super Club Cable. He also plays regularly at Voyage Voyage in up and coming Berlin venue Salon Zur Wilden Renate.
His productions, alongside fellow Hardway Bros, Jake Davies and a mysterious South Londoner known only as Rico have graced Sabres of Paradise, Third Mind, Flashcomm and more recently Beard Science, Pointless Edits, Aniligital, History Clock, Astrolab and cult Norwegian act Mungolian Jetset's label Luna Flicks. 
 
Sean's DJ'ing style described by FACT Magazine as "Future Disco" is hard to pin down to one convenient genre, taking in house, disco, re-edits, techno and frankly anything else that takes his fancy. 
 
Alongside Andrew Weatherall he runs and DJ's at A Love From Outer Space, a cult monthly residency at The Drop in North London. The night's manifesto is to never knowingly exceed 122bpm and is home to a multitude of genres including ambient, balearica, dub, krautrock, post punk, proto house, un-disco and other curiosities from the pair's extensive record collections.

\\ These spiritual window-shoppers,
      who idly ask, 'How much is that?' Oh, I'm just looking.
      They handle a hundred items and put them down,
      shadows with no capital.

       What is spent is love and two eyes wet with weeping.
      But these walk into a shop,
      and their whole lives pass suddenly in that moment,
      in that shop.

       Where did you go? "Nowhere."
      What did you have to eat? "Nothing much."

       Even if you don't know what you want,
      buy _something,_ to be part of the exchanging flow.

       Start a huge, foolish project,
      like Noah.

       It makes absolutely no difference
      what people think of you.

Bio:
In the years since its conception in 2006, Prosthetic has grown from a humble bedroom label to an internationally known driving force. Prosthetic focuses on volatile, left field techno that showcases talents from around the world. Always evolving their cultural identity, Prosthetic maintains its credibility in the Chicago community by the continuous enthusiasm and perseverance for dance music. 
Now in their 5th year, Prosthetic's profile must once again take a forward step into the future. Plaguing charts and their ever growing roster have helped to develop a relationship with Chicago's premier techno venue, Smart Bar, showing the support from this legendary city. Prosthetic is able to showcase their global roster and has now become home to the underground and its artistic vanguards within the electronic community.

His sound has earned him in-crew-sion in Seth Troxler’s Tuskegee posse, Green Velvet’s Relief Records, and of course Tiga's Turbo. With years of releases under his belt, he’s maintained an impressively consistent voice. 
​
It all comes down to the fact that he is a bonafide sex addict who managed to turn a problem into a career by combining his obsession with thickness and his prowess for production. His Releases can be heard as Harvard Bass’ confession, his plea of insanity set to the sound of a perfectly functioning Ibiza super-club, complete with sexy paid dancers, industrial smoke cannons, and the kind of mass communal ego death that comes from 10+ straight hours of tech-house.
 
With the Launch of his very own Bump City Records, Harvard has vowed to put his famous raw ghetto sexiness on the map. Boom-time, ladies and gentlemen.

The social netlabel among the clouds.
Dirigibl is a decentralized netlabel based entirely around social networks and focusing on electronic music for home listening.
Dirigibl is in its beta phase. This includes building a community and developing tracks for its debut compilation release. The idea is to use social networks as a platform and crowdsourcing as a concept to put together a Creative Commons backed netlabel. You can be a contributer, a fan, an A&R rep, a remixer, or a sound designer. You can add as little or as much as you like. Let's get some people together and see where this goes.

Rennie Foster has been a well-respected figure in the Canadian music and art community for over two decades. He influenced many as an early pioneer of the Hip-Hop / B-Boy movement, and later the House Music and Techno / Rave scene, participating in the first events in Western Canada during the birth of these now common urban subcultures. He is also very well known within the niche of graffiti art for his early work, having been archived in several published books.

Rennie relocated to Tokyo Japan in 2004 and became an important part of the Japanese club scene, playing all over Japan in venues such as Womb, ageHa, and Yellow, maintaining DJ residencies in Tokyo and Kyoto at the Metro club and at the Nagisa Music Festival in Tokyo and Osaka. Rennie was consistently ranked in the top 50 DJs in Japan by LOUD Magazine until re-locating back to Canada in 2011. Rennie is currently a resident DJ at Western Canada’s top after-hours club, Gorg-O-Mishin Vancouver, BC, regularly traveling to play as a guest at underground venues across Canada, Detroit, New York,and Paris and has played festivals such as Shambhala and  Bass Coast among others.

Rennie Foster has released music with Jack White’s Third Man Label, classic dance music labels including Transmat, F-Communications, Synewave, Teknotika, Subject Detroit, and is widely recognized for his underground anthem Devil's Water on Rebirth Records. Rennie has remixed, or been remixed by, some of the top names in dance music such as Juan Atkins, James Zabiela and Swayzak. He has released many singles, EPs, and four full length albums. He runs a signature record label RF and continues to produce tough urban house music and stylish techno for cutting edge dance music imprint including Goldmin Music and Skylax Records in Paris and the Detroit based Soiree Records.

 
“Get yourself acquainted with Mr.Foster quick-smart” – DJ magazine, UK.

"Rennie Foster rules the underground." - Georgia Straight, CA.

Ray Okpara - An artist whose roots lie half in Nigeria represents today for what we understand as House: 

Percussions, drifty hypnotic beats, a touch of soul and marvellously deep.........house is a feeling and Ray Okpara has his finger firmly on the pulse, leading the way. Whilst his own roots are in Nigeria, it is actually Mannheim, Germany that Ray has helped put on the electronic music map, with a string of stellar productions on hot labels like Cécille, Oslo, Get Physical, Soweso and Arearemote and an indomitable DJ style that has seen him rock out the world’s great modern clubbing arenas.

With Ray’s distinctive style, it’s no surprise to learn that his early influences were hip-hop, funk and soul before the nightlife escapades of he and long-time friend Johnny D truly awoke his strong interest in electronic music. Impressed by the many different genres, the first attempt on the turntables was actually using Johnny's UK Garage Records. But the passion was sparked and Ray and Johnny began their own party, RAJO, which was hugely popular throughout the Rhein Necker Delta.

Another friend, Nick Curly, joined RAJO in 2001 and 'The Loft’ residency began in Mannheim, where the first seeds of something monumental were unwittingly being sown. The Mannheim influence, and the time Ray has spent living there, is tangible; during these years the technical elements of Ray’s sets developed and the groove began to take shape, thankfully encompassing all the early influences like soul and funk.

Berlin was calling in 2005 and beginning 4 years living in the city, Ray really started to blossom musically. The heralded DJ performances were soon accompanied by productions, such as remixes for Johnny D on Oslo and 8-bit or the Italoboyz on Get Physical. His first EP, ‘Fumnaya’ on Lomidhigh Lmtd and releases like ‘Frozen on Yellow Ice’ (Arearemote) and ‘Loving Moonbauh’ (Drumpoet Community) were instrumental in Mannheim’s explosion in 2008.  

On returning to Mannheim in 2009, his Brothers EP (Oslo) was a permanent fixture in clubs across the world in in the first half of the year and is one of the 2009’s most charted tracks on Resident Advisor. On the brink of beginning his live act in 2010, two further EPs, ‘Brainows’ on Soweso and ‘Tru Crowd’ back on Area Remote put Ray Okpara on the front foot going into a new decade of continued house grooves and more good times.

A crowd teaser and crowd pleaser, constantly rocking it with music to make you smile and lose yourself in the moment, Ray Okpara is coming to get you and there is no hiding place. 

House music still movin’ and groovin’.........

Rays Recordlabel:
Ama Recordings is Ray Okpara’s label out of Mannheim, Germany. Amaefule, Ray’s middle name in fact, literally means “your name will never get lost” and it symbolizes the strength of identity we create through music. Ama is also derived from the Latin meaning of love and the philosophy of the label is born out of the affection held for conceiving and sharing quality electronic music. There are no rules about what Ama Recordings will sound like, but it comes from the heart, so expect true house values to be maintained at all times with a natural tip towards the deep and dubby.

Pop Metal from Liechtenstein! Imagine a groovy rock band that combines a pop singers voice with modern electronic sounds and low tuned, heavy guitars and you will exactly get what Downfall is all about: Pop Metal with catchy songs and a pack of power! Downfall was founded in 1999 in the tiny Principality of Liechtenstein. With its total population of around 30,000 and landlocked by Switzerland and Austria, the country does not only domicile various bank houses but also some fine rock bands. The four guys started as a cover band, mainly reinterpreting synth pop songs of acts such as Depeche Mode, Tears For Fears or A-Ha in a modern rock style. This first chapter was crowned in 2002 with an EP named Wonderful Life - A Tribute To Pop. Since then, the band started writing original songs. In April 2007, Downfall released their new, selftitled EP. It was once again produced by ex-Coroner mainman and producer Tommy Vetterli in Zürich, Switzerland. In August of the same year, the band won a band contest held by national radio station Radio Liechtenstein with the song Sorrow from their current EP voted as Best Song International. Downfall consists of singer Mathias Nutt, guitarist Johannes Schraner, drummer Marius Matt and bassist & sound designer Thomas Hemmi. For more information as well as press photos check the official website www.downfall.li.

Multitasking, double layering, over dubbing. In 15 years of live-therapy with KiEw we have realized that one single personality just won't do, the multiple characters just came with that discovery. That's where the road of the chameleon for the ?**? began and we guess it will refuse to end at a single location.
Now why it sounds the way it does, we simply do not know, especially not why we branded it "Industrial" also, but we guess whoever did that, he or she must have had a reason for it. For now we just recommend to turn to rant radio once in a while, listen to the monkey and join in on the live therapy in station Odessa. Don't be muteful and fruit fly

Seven years after Fool Again, musician, producer and dj Rafael Garnica, better known as @Garnica, returns to the scene with "The Spirit". This new single has marked the first release since the premiere of his debut album in 2013.
 
The native artist of the Venezuelan Andes, who was a drummer in @submarino2001 and @galgosound , is currently based in the Spanish city of Barcelona, from where he continues to work and produce new tracks.
 
In addition to these projects, Garnica has also remained active in the Barcelona scene under the pseudonym @kiss_me_again, a proposal that has a sound described as "Versatile Balearic House with some downtempo". His most recent work is an edit of the song "Nights Over Egypt” from The Jones Girls.
 
In combination with this pair of artistic projects, the former drummer is the host of "Legacy", a podcast to enjoy music classics refined by DJs and selectors in stylised sessions.
 
To keep up to date with all the news about Garnica and his projects, visit http://aboutgarnica.com/

And my totally accurate bio:
Just a wandering man of music, ever in search of his own voice.  I'm no longer chasing the elusive "success" of musical stardom.  You see, I feel I've already found that success.  When I sit in my backyard strumming my guitar or up on my roof strumming my violin or in my bedroom strumming my tinwhistle or whatever, I know what success, happiness and peace truly are.  It's still difficult, though, when I break a string on my guitar and can't afford to buy a new one or run out of rosin for my cheap violin and have to use dried tree sap or accidentally sit on my ten dollar tinwhistle, bend it, and can't afford to bend it straight again.  I'm sure that most "successful" musicians could just call their manager or whoever in those instances and they'd be taken care of.  Not me, though.  Also, it's difficult when I try to give away my CDs and nobody wants them, or when I bake all day in the hot sun playing on the sidewalk, and nobody gives me a dime.  Also, I can't get real gigs.  Musicians that are "in demand" just have a booking agent who does that for them, and they never have any trouble.  They probably make like twenty grand every time they play a gig.  I'd be happy with just a free meal.  I'd be happy with any meal, anywhere.  My years as a musician have taught me that simplicity is bliss.  I have simple needs.  I'd even eat your leftovers, if you're not finished with that.  A great Irish poet once said that we are all of us in the gutter, but only a few are looking at the stars.  Well, I can't look at the stars--my face is being ground into the muck at the bottom of this gutter!
                
                Soundcloud is the latest in a lifelong series of huge dreams that I'm hoping will get me out of the mess I'm in and take me to the next level.  The next level for me will be pretty much anything that's better than being burned alive.  I love the internet, it's taken me so many place that I can't afford to go.  I feel like I've seen the world, shared my music in all the greatest cities on earth.  I know for a fact that some people from other countries have seen my myspace page.  Nobody's willing to pay, though.  I keep sending out bulletins to all of my friends on myspace, saying that I'll take wire transfers in exchange for a real signed copy of my CD, but it just hasn't happened yet.  I'm trying to figure out now how to make soundcloud a lucrative endeavor.  I think this is my lucky break, getting invited into this thing.  Thank you all so much, and look forward to hearing some great music once I get all of my instruments out of the pawn shop.  Well, hopefully I'll be able to get some of them.  I didn't go in soon enough to get my accordion, and they sold it, which is lousy.  I just found out it was worth like two grand, and I only got a hundred and fifty bucks!  I'm trying to take them to court, but I can't afford a lawyer.  Check back here regularly to see if I've figured out a way to set up a legal representation fund so you can donate to the cause.  You know I'm in the right on this one.

Emanating from south London's "Hilly Fields of Lewisham", Sarah Williams White is a singer songwriter, multi-instrumentalist and producer. 
After a string of self-released singles and live tours including UK support for Dan Le Sac vs Scroobious Pip and Lex Record's Golden Rules, her debut album was released in November 2015 on local label First Word Records; written, produced and performed by Sarah in her home studio, with the addition of formidable breaks drummer, engineer and husband Timmy Rickard. The fantastical 'Of The New World' mini album presented a uniquely intimate talent to the experimental soul underground, one with earthy spirit and one that is boldly herself.

Succeeded by a number of songwriting collaborations including with brother producer Paul White (Danny Brown, Sudan Archives), Williams-White further demonstrates her instinct for an off-centre catchy hook.

2022 will see a return from the Londoner with her signature buttery lathering of vocals, cutting beats and atypical pop sensibilities. 
Her forthcoming solo record 'Unfathomable' offers up escapism from the mundane, enticing us to connect with our natural planet in this prevalent time, via the eyes of a new mother. Sarah is establishing herself as one of the UK's most interesting and irresistible experimental pop talents. 

Some praise for Sarah Willimas White:

"Absolutely beautiful" - Lauren Laverne,  BBC 6 Music
"New and special" - Jamie Cullum,  BBC Radio 2
"A shining and soulful sonic odyssey" -  The 405
"Dark, feminine, chaotic & beautiful" -  The Guardian

Born in Belize and raised in New York City. MKL has a wide spectrum of influence embedded in his art. As a DJ, his desire to blend genres and flex his appreciation for music is focused around community – the end goal is to bring people together. “It was the mixing aspect that really drew me in,” he says. “The ability to take people on a journey via projection of one’s own vibe was the art form I fell in love with.” After twenty years behind the decks and about ten as a producer, Michael K Lopez founded Lion1Music, which serves as the ultimate outlet for his vision as an artist in the electronic music community.

MKL’s original material started with 3 Generations Walking, a production effort shared with Herman Pearl, a.k.a. Soy Sos. The pair’s debut, Skin, was released on Buddah Bar, At the same time, the duo began releasing remixes and MKL’s first contribution to Wave Music – the celebrated label founded by the legendary Francois K – was remixing Calm’s “People From The Earth & The Sun” with Soy Sos, which was released on a single alongside a remix from Dixon. Shortly after that, the 3 Generations team worked on “Slavery Days"  out  Spiritual Life Music, a label that combined world music and soulful house. “Slavery Days” got over ten licensing agreements and was included on the highly influential “ Body & Soul Vol. 4"

“Seven Times” – Lion1Music’s first release in 2004 – was a 12” that blended future jazz and deep house and utilized the production chemistry that had developed between Michael Lopez and Herman Pearl.  
 "The goal is to bring different musical communities together under one banner and, in the process, increase the global awareness of Lion1Music,” explains MKL. “We’re a progressive label for progressive music of all genres.” Tastemakers at major record labels soon became of MKL’s abilities which in turn have led to remixes for John Legend (“Green Light”).

MKL’s newest release, “Forever Love” is indicative of his emerging sound, blending deep house, techno and infectious chord progressions. When not in the studio MKL has been busy plying his trade behind the turntables both internationally and domestically. Recent ports of calls for the musical wanderer have included Japan, France, Moscow and Tulum. When at home he spins at some of the hottest nightspots in the Big Apple including Output, Cielo and Le Bain. The summer months sees MKL juggle a busy schedule of high end private bookings in the Hamptons & NYC, where he has recently spun at Gotham Hall, ST Regis & SoHi.

Goh Nakamura is a singer, songwriter, musician, composer and actor. His guitar work has been featured in films directed by Ridley Scott such as A Good Year, American Gangster and Body of Lies. His track "Daylight Savings" also appears in the film Feast of Love. Nakamura made his acting debut in Dave Boyle's award-winning film, Surrogate Valentine, where he played a fictionalized version of himself. The film screened at a number of festivals including the SXSW Film Festival and Nakamura won a Special Jury Prize for Acting from the Dallas International Film Festival for his performance in it. 

Nakamura's first album is entitled Daylight Savings.[5] A music video directed by Dino Ignacio for a track on that album entitled "Embarcadero Blues" became featured on the frontpage of YouTube and soon amassed over 1 million views.[6] The title track of the album, "Daylight Savings" was also featured on the soundtrack for the 2007 film Feast of Love, directed by Robert Benton, based on the Charles Baxter novel of the same name and starring Morgan Freeman, Greg Kinnear, Selma Blair and many others.[7]

Nakamura also co-wrote the lyrics for the song "Bird's Eye", performed and also co-written by Mike Patton, Serj Tankian and film composer Marc Streitenfeld, which was a featured song on the original soundtrack for Ridley Scott's 2008 film, Body of Lies.[8][9] Nakamura has also contributed bass & guitar music to the score of Ridley Scott's American Gangster and also guitar and vocals to the score of another Ridley Scott film, A Good Year.

Nakamura's second album is entitled Ulyssess and was considered more of a "branching out" in style that received positive reviews from the likes of KQED.[10] Nakamura's third album is entitled Motion from the Music Picture and features songs from Dave Boyle's films Surrogate Valentine and Daylight Savings.

Gabriel Palomo’s passion for electronic music spans the history of his deep roots in rhythm, sound, and dance. Playing the drums since the late 70’s and spinning vinyl through space since the early 80’s, evolving through the journeys of old school hip hop break-dance beats, Italo-classics, early electro, acid-house and techno, Driven by the amazing energy of techno music, Gabriel brings years of life experience and musical skills to the electronic music scene.

 

His production has fueled his own record labels – Zuvuya Recordings and Linear, in addition to other labels such as Chicago Jaxxx, Rheostatus, Elephanthaus, and Fresca Recordings. Lookout for upcoming releases on his newly launched label LVLZ and on Format.  With driving techno syncopation and hard acid electro qualities, his tracks have been charted, played and licensed by the likes of Dave Clarke, DJ Hell, Mauro Piccotto, Felix Da Housecat, Tommie Sunshine, and DJ T-1000, just to name a few. Remix projects include tracks by The Horrorist, and Tim Xavier.

 

Out of the studio, he’s played an integral role in keeping Chicago's techno scene throwing underground and public events his promotional leadership of EnvironMental Sound Therapists, the Conjugate Projekt (best known for the unprecedented moving train party Motion-ness), along with 773 Tekno Saturdays (w/ Tim Xavier), In Your System! (w/ Blueline records and Majestic), Noisefloor, and Format.

“As her moniker implies, she takes no prisoners, channeling the fury instilled by worldly injustices into blistering, defiant sets." - Mixmag 2017

Raised in small-town Indiana on a musical diet of 80s synth pop and punk rock, Noncompliant soon found barnyard raves and warehouse techno parties and (as DJ Shiva) quickly became a fixture of the fabled 90s Midwest USA rave scene.

Two decades and a name change later, she is at the top of her techno game. Mixmag named her one of 2017’s Top 20 Breakthrough DJs. She owned a packed and sweaty Boiler Room during Movement Detroit, turned in mindblowing mixes for Slam Radio, Discwoman, and Resident Advisor, and quaked some of the world’s most respected dance floors like Smartbar Chicago, Amsterdam’s DeSchool, Concrete in Paris, and Berlin's legendary Berghain and Tresor clubs. Her festival appearances include Unsound, Red Bull Music Festival Paris, Movement Detroit, and Whole United Queer Festival.

As a producer, her releases and remixes on labels like Valence, Argot, Flash, and Dark Entries have pounded sound systems worldwide, with her tune “Women’s Work” landing on Fiedel’s official Berghain 08 mix and on his label Fiedeltwo.

At her core, she is a die-hard techno fan with a deep love for music and a drive to continue honing her craft as a DJ and producer to share her favorite music with people on dance floors everywhere.

A great track is a great track, regardless of the genre. It is this philosophy combined with a profound love of sharing music that has allowed Kered to entertain crowds on the sun-drenched beaches of Ibiza to the clubs of Berlin, Montreal, Los Angeles, Munich and more.
Kered has released music on acclaimed labels such as Definitive Recordings, Nervous Records, Witty Tunes and ultimately on his own label, Loot Recordings. With a passion for discovering new sounds, Loot Recordings has become a platform for new artists to release their music together with established artists who have become a part of the label’s family.

In the DJ booth, Kered’s sound is all about the dance floor. Armed with a deep arsenal and collection of music, Kered’s sets reflect a deeper, emotional sound that’s combined with peak hour rhythms and some classic favorites. Influenced by early Detroit techno and Chicago house, a typical Kered set knows no boundaries and is weaved together to tell a complete story from start to finish.

The adventure continues and we invite you to experience Kered’s celebratory spirit of dance music that’s fused together with beautiful melodies, driving rhythms and the sound of today’s club culture. Let’s get lost in the music together…

We promise to be serious at least some of the time. 
  
  Sincerely,
  
  The Railyard Crew

American Bryan Cox started his internationally acclaimed career back when vinyl was king.  A long dedication to his craft, bridging different genres, and with many successful aliases, Cox continues forward with his funk based take on tech house and house music.  Along his career he’s collected 5 star magazine write ups, numerous #1s on Beatport and other stores in both digital and vinyl format, top DJ and radio support, an international DJ schedule,  TV show placement, multiple mix CDs, various musical awards, and most importantly respect from his peers.  Bryan’s releases come on some of the world’s most respected labels including Spinnin’, Toolroom, 100% Pure, Defected, Hotfingers, Ministry of Sound, Great Stuff, Subliminal, and many more.  His music is continually supported by some of the top names in electronic music today.

Bryan Cox also created the PHNTM project which also came to internationl fame.  PHNTM has released on some of the industry's top labels including: Blanco y Negro, Toolroom, 1605, Great Stuff, Hotfingers, Definitive, BluFin, and many more. PHNTM has received prestigious recognition from the music community such as Beatport’s Artist to Watch and being nominated for a Beatport Music Award. His popular genre blending style of Commercial Disco and Groovy Tech-Funk also received great success on the Beatport charts, with multiple #1's, reaching as high as #4 overall with his Umek collaboration "Dead Space". PHNTM has performed at some of the most premier events in the world such as the Ultra Music Festival in Miami and the famous BCM in Mallorca. 

Cox has toured the world from Asia, Europe, North and South America playing at some of the top clubs and festivals including Ultra, Dance Valley, DEM, Ambasada Gavioli, Ice Las Vegas, Beats 4 Love, Bee Free and many more.  Bryan Cox continues to develop his unique funk fueled take on House and Tech House music with a lot of exciting releases dropping soon.

Giovanni Moscatello believe it or not it..s his real name. His roots are Sicilian but hes born and raised in Germany and based in Berlin for the past six Years. He grew up with electronic music. As a child he listened to the music of his brother Fillipo known as DJ Naughty. So Chicago House and Detroit Techno has been early influences. 1993 he began to work in a record store and two years later he started to spin the turntables as a DJ. His sound is unique a combination of his Italian temper and his classic roots driven by his love for music and feeling for the crowd. 2004 his first release came out .. Error Records featuring Adrien Walter (Sex in Dallas), which was followed by two releases on the greek Netlabel DIGILOG.GR. The latest cooperation with Berlin based "Dj Stuffit" already has a huge amount of tracks which will be released starting from june..08 till the end of the year in a monthly cycle on different labels. Also he is promoting his "Moscatello..s DISCO Mafia"events now since more then a year with a uprising number of people every month in different locations in Berlin. Some interesting events are scheduled in May and later in the summer. Check the website for upcoming dates and more information. As a Dj he spins regulary in different locations across town, as the legendary "Tresor" or the "Pulp Mansion" up to numerous underground locations as the Stereo 33, Fire Club just to name a few. Giovanni is also one part of DONNER & MOSCATELLO. The idea of working together with Martin Donner came up when both met each other at a DJ gig and sharing a drunk night. They came along perfectly well - both on a personal and a musical level. DONNER & MOSCATELLO present modern electronic dance music, always putting the power and will for party first. Style is the key. Due to their versatile musical interests and their feeling for the audience - both artists are disposed to excessive parties and musical surprises. Watch out for their releases. Giovanni always guarantees for a good and stabile crowd on the dancefloor. With his knowledge to select and spin records he drove dancefloors across europe already insane. His natural temper leads him always to experiments with the latest releases of different kinds and his collection of Disco, House and Acid. "let your body learn to jack the house".
James is the label manager of Amsterdam based Strøm recordings and together with Mike we produce and DJ a mix of tech-house, progressive and trance music.

DOC RECORDS is an independent record label founded in 2013 and operated by Brazilian architect and music producer Gui Boratto. The name is a reference to "Denominazione Di Origine Controllata" or D.O.C., used for certifying all different types of food which follow a set of regulations and come from specific geographical areas. In this case, it's about music that relates to Gui's own sound-like principles: to Gui, more important than style, it is the music itself that and its beauty and harmony that count the most. Thus, the intent to launch quality timeless music, avant-garde, rhetorical and with a well defined and efficient language and expression, regardless of its shell. 

After all, there's only good or bad taste.

I was fortunate to be around NYC for the Illbient scene in the mid 90s, and for years played dark ambient and experimental/ psychedelic sounds all over town, including Twilo, The Kitchen, and The Brooklyn Museum. I co-hosted the weekly chillout party Undercity for four years at the original Halcyon. A big part of the reason I came to Berlin was to play bigdarkcrazytrippy techno, which I flavor heavily with the ambient tools and more. I make sounds for the freaks.

Along with Dr. Walker (Air Liquide), Omsk Information, adsx, and others, I am a resident on lsb_tv, Liquid Sky Berlin's weekly chillout tv/radio/web show on alex-berlin.de. Please tune in every Saturday from midnight to 6am, Berlin time.

for most DJ sets, a screengrab of the Ableton session is available on my website, so you can see what's happening: always lots of layers.

Eyes, ears, and mind are open. Rules and criteria do not apply. The objective is not a plot for status. It is a personal journey. An investigation into what can be done within a chosen framework. A reflection of myself into sound.
